post_text:
TFC administration encourages families to come out and support our football teams whenever possible. Now, more than ever, safety and supervision of children is a priority. Our bond project makes the grounds around our stands potentially hazardous for unattended children. TFC does not provide supervision during athletic events. Parents are responsible for their children’s supervision and safety. Children need to remain in the stands to watch the game with their parents. We do not allow children to play or loiter in any way behind the stadium or near the concession stand; nor is it appropriate to have the children playing in the end zones. The end zones need to be kept clear at all times for emergency vehicles. Students who continue to disregard this policy will be recorded and have consequences at school.

Thank you in advance for your support and cooperation.
TFC Administrators

post_text:
Summer Weights Training Schedule:

Starting Tuesday, June 2nd at the TFC School weight room.

Weight training days will be Monday, Tuesday, and Thursday.

There will be three different sessions a week held on those days, and will last approximately one hour each.

The weight room will be cleaned after each session.

There will be training at three different times to keep the group size smaller.

Each session is designed for specific groups, but athletes can attend whatever session is most convenient.

Weight training is for a students who will be entering 7th - 12th grade for the 2020-2021 school year.

Times:
8:00 a.m. - 9:00 a.m. - 9th-12th grade boys.
9:15 a.m. - 10:15 a.m. - All girls.
10:30 a.m. - 11:30 a.m. - 7th - 8th grade boys.

For any student that needs to lift.

post_text: Reminder - We are still collecting school supply fees for for the 2020-2021 school year. The final deadline is Friday, May 8th. post_text: Congratulations, Connor!
shared_text:
Weatherford Daily News
March 30 at 10:11 AM ·

Southwestern Oklahoma State University student Connor Slattery of Weatherford was selected to represent SWOSU at the 2020 Oklahoma Research Day at the Capitol in Oklahoma City.

But, because of the COVID-19 outbreak, the 25th annual event for Oklahoma’s legislators was cancelled.

Slattery, a student of Dr. Rickey Cothran in the Department of Biological Sciences, was selected by the University Research and Scholarly Activity Committee, chaired by Dr. Lisa Appeddu and facilitated by the Office of Sponsored Programs.

Slattery was one of 22 undergraduate students representing 16 Oklahoma colleges and universities who were identified to participate in the prestigious event, which is designed to raise awareness of the outstanding undergraduate research that is taking place at Oklahoma’s colleges and universities.

Slattery’s research project focused on water quality.

Research Day is sponsored by the National Science Foundation, Oklahoma NSF Established Program to Stimulate Competitive Research, and the Oklahoma State Regents for Higher Education.

Thank you!
TFC Administration

Thomas-Fay-Custer Schools is excited to announce that we now have a new app to make it easier to get information and updates through the school!

Just go to your App Store in your phone, and type in “Thomas Fay Custer Schools” and the “TFC Schools” app will appear. Just download the app for free, and be sure to turn on your notifications for the app, so you can receive important updates as they are made available through the school.

If you still cannot find it through the app store, you can go to our website, and there are instructions and links on there to download the app.

Thank you!

shared_text:
Weatherford Food & Resource Center
July 31, 2019 at 4:40 PM ·

Thomas-Fay-Custer Schools cheerleaders volunteered at WFRC today. They swept and mopped the market, halls, and offices, they cleaned the bathrooms, hung up flyers, organized grocery bags, organized the office supply closet, and giggled the entire time. These girls served with gladness in their hearts and we enjoyed every minute of their gift of time. All the dirty work that these ladies did today is necessary to #FIGHTHUNGER and #FEEDHOPE. Thank you, #TFCCheer! 💚
.
.
.
#servewithjoy #servewithgladness #cheerleaders #TFCTerriers #ThomasTerriers #hungerfighters #GoFightWin #cheerleadersdoinggood
#ThomasOK #FayOK #CusterCityOK

Important Notice about Little Olympics (please share):
Due to change in weather, we are adjusting times & locations of some field events for Little Olympics tomorrow, Friday, May 10th. The a.m. schedule will start with:

8:30 a.m. —-5G, 5B, 6G, 6B
Shot Put

Approximately 9:00 a.m.:
3G, 3B, 4G, 4B, 5G, 5B, 6G, 6B
High Jump

KG, KB, 1G, 1B, 2G, 2B:
Distance Kick

All in the Old Gym.

After this, we will assess the weather situation. If time allows before lunch & weather is not favorable, we will continue with softball throw & football throw in the old gym. Lunch break will still be from 11:00 a.m. -12:00 p.m. We apologize for any inconvenience & thank you for your understanding.

Dear Parents —

Our school has officially started Kids Heart Challenge with the American Heart Association. Help us fight heart disease by earning our heart heroes Echo, Finn and Ruby right now! As a special BONUS at our school you can also earn plush FINN, by raising $150 online by 5 AM on 2/22/2019!
Students who earn plush Finn will be recognized on this day! Get started now by downloading our APP called Kids Heart Challenge for iPhone and Android OR go online to the link below to View Our School Webpage and Sign up (you can earn a glow in the dark bracelet just for registering).

http://www2.heart.org/site/TR?fr_id=3999&pg=company&company_id=193317

Go to this link to watch the heart-healthy experience that students are having at school: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=iGs25gWtPBw&feature=youtu.be

· Thomas-Fay-Custer Elementary’s Kids Heart Challenge event day is: 2/28/2019

· Donations are due: 2/28/2019

Any help would be appreciated!
We had a great year last year! We raised over $8,700 last year and won the Rookie of the Year award!

Thank you!
